Saint-Etienne have announced the signing of former Sevilla centre-back Timothee Kolodziejczak from Tigres UANL after impressing the French club on loan last season.

As Inter are still hoping to land Arturo Vidal, according to Mundo Deportivo. Barcelona have rejected a loan offer from the Italians but would accept a fee of 13 million euros.

And following the loan signing of Kubo from Real Madrid, Mallorca have continued their summer spree by bringing in Yannis Salibur from Guingamp on a three-year deal.



			
